library(shiny)
library(shinydashboard)
library(ggplot2)
library(lubridate)
library(DT)
library(jpeg)
library(grid)
library(leaflet)
library(scales)

#read .csv file
litter2 <- read.table(file = "litterati challenge-65.csv", sep = ",", header = TRUE)

# convert lat and lon to int
litter2$lat <- as.numeric(as.character(litter2$lat))
litter2$lon <- as.numeric(as.character(litter2$lon))

# remove outliers
litter <- subset(litter2, (lat > 41.849783 & lat < 41.888720) & (lon < -87.803481 & lon > -87.833827) )

#name untagged info
litter$tags <- sub("^$", "untagged", litter$tags)

#convert to lubridate chicago time format
litter$litterTimestamp <-ymd_hms(litter$litterTimestamp, tz = "GMT")
litter$litterTimestamp <-with_tz(litter$litterTimestamp, tz = "America/Chicago")
#litter$litterTimestamp <- newdates

#adding cols to data frame bar chart
litter$dayoftheweek <- wday(litter$litterTimestamp, label = TRUE) 

litter$date <- date(litter$litterTimestamp) 

litter$hour <- hour(litter$litterTimestamp) 

#Total litter collected
totalLitter <- NROW(litter)

#generate table of most frequent days
litter.table_datefreq <- as.data.frame(table(litter$date))
litter.table_datefreq <- litter.table_datefreq[order(litter.table_datefreq$Freq,  decreasing=TRUE), ]

#generate table of top users
litter.table_topusers <- as.data.frame(table(litter$username))
litter.table_topusers <- litter.table_topusers[order(litter.table_topusers$Freq,  decreasing=TRUE), ]

#generate table of days of the week
litter.table_topdays <- as.data.frame(table(litter$dayoftheweek))
litter.table_topdays <- litter.table_topdays[order(litter.table_topdays$Freq,  decreasing=TRUE), ]

#generate table of hours of the day
litter.table_tophours <- as.data.frame(table(litter$hour))
litter.table_tophours <- litter.table_tophours[order(litter.table_tophours$Freq,  decreasing=TRUE), ]

unique_tag_list <- as.list(unique(litter$tags)) #extract all unique tags, pre-parse
unique_tag_string <- gsub(" ", ",", paste(unique_tag_list, collapse=' ')) #long string parsable now by commas
unique_tag_vec <- strsplit(unique_tag_string, ",") #now all in 1 vector of indivisual strings, 6907 long

#generate table for most frequent tags
tagstable.table <- as.data.frame(table(unique_tag_vec))
tagstable.table <- tagstable.table[order(tagstable.table$unique_tag_vec, decreasing=TRUE), ]
 

ggplot(litter.table_topdays, aes(x=Var1, y=Freq)) + geom_bar(stat="identity", fill="steelblue") +
  labs(x="Day of the Week", y = "Amount of Litter")
